    <h1>Pick list</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can use plentymarkets to generate pick lists as PDF or CSV files, for example if you want to import them into another software.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_displaying_item_data">1. Displaying item data</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the <strong>pick list</strong> menu to specify which item data should be included on your pick list, e.g. the item ID, EAN, storage location, etc and how this information should be displayed.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/order-processing/orders/order-documents/assets/EN-Settings-Orders-Documents-Pick-List-01.png" alt="EN Settings Orders Documents Pick List 01">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 1: settings in the <strong>Pick list</strong> menu</em></p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Showing and hiding fields</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a position number for every field that you want to <strong>display</strong>. If you do not want to display a field on the pick list, then select <strong>----</strong> as the <strong>position</strong></p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying item data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Orders » Documents » Pick list</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Decide which fields should be displayed on the pick list. Decide which order these fields should be displayed in. This is done by assigning a <strong>position number</strong> to each field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make changes to the field names as desired. You can enter your customized text under <strong>Name</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Specify how <strong>wide</strong> the fields should be. Choose which <strong>font size</strong> and <strong>font style</strong> should be used for the texts.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in the following table and carry out any additional settings as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Top margin</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a value (in mm) for the <strong>top margin</strong> on the page. Change the value if needed. For example, change the value if you use a PDF template that contains the company information and logo at the top of the page and you want to position this "header" above the pick list (see section 3 below).</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Storage location</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>If you use this field, then decide how the <strong>storage location name</strong> should be displayed on the pick list. For example, only the storage location name can be displayed or various combinations of warehouse information can be displayed, such as the rack / shelf / storage location. The quantity is displayed next to the storage location by default. Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Do not show the quantity next to the storage location</strong> if you do not want to display this information on the pick list.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Free text</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the name for the free text field. In other words, enter the name that should be displayed on the pick list and select the corresponding <strong>free text field 1-20</strong> from the drop-down menu.<br>
First, go to <strong>Settings » Item » Free text fields</strong> to create the free text fields. Then link the corresponding items to the free text fields and enter values for the fields. Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » Tab: Fields</strong> to do so.<br>
For further information, refer to the <strong><a href=":/">Free text fields</a></strong> and the <strong><a href=":/">Fields</a></strong> pages of the manual.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Item description</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Decide which information should be included in the item description. The <strong>item name</strong> is always displayed with this field. It is also possible to include additional information, e.g. the <strong>storage location</strong> (see the option above), <strong>item ID</strong>, <strong>external item ID</strong>, <strong>item number</strong>, <strong>EAN</strong> and <strong>order properties</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Table 1: options in the <strong>Pick list</strong> menu</em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you select the settings as shown in image 1, then the pick list that is generated will look like this:</p>
</div>
